{"ts":"2026-06-27T22:36:09.691Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"wj710ss8","input":{"summary":"Completed task 181-phase6-frontend-env-and-api-finalization successfully.\n1. Designed and created `components/ApiBaseUrlInterceptor.tsx` client-side component to intercept all fetch requests targeting local `/api/v1` routes in portal or admin routes, prefixing them with the configured `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` backend base URL when defined.\n2. Mounted the `<ApiBaseUrlInterceptor />` in the root layout `app/layout.tsx` so that it seamlessly handles API traffic on all client pages.\n3. Configured `app/portal/documents/page.tsx` and `app/admin/documents/page.tsx` to conditionally hide/show upload buttons, the administrative register asset trigger, and the high-fidelity drag-and-drop secure client dropzone based on the `NEXT_PUBLIC_PORTAL_UPLOADS_ENABLED` feature flag.\n4. Hardened security inside `components/private-app/PreviewRouteGuard.tsx` and `components/portal/SecureLogin.tsx` by rejecting local mock preview logins and automatic mock fallbacks in production environments (`NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_ENV === \"production\"`), ensuring strict JWT auth with the actual FastAPI backend is enforced.\n5. Confirmed that GFF AI build tools and the approved landing page remain completely unaffected.\n6. Verified everything compile and lint cleanly with zero ESLint errors and zero TypeScript compile errors.","verified":true}}}
